        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:50PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pinnacle, or near Pilot Mountain, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
King...
Pinnacle...
Pilot Mountain State Park...
Germanton...
and Capella.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
